  "prompt": "How much money per hour do Uber drivers make in Des Moines? What's the most a person can reasonably make per month?",
  "response": "The amount of money Uber drivers make can vary significantly based on factors like location, demand, time of day, and individual driving habits. In Des Moines, Iowa, drivers often report earnings ranging from $15 to $25 per hour before expenses. These expenses can include gas, vehicle maintenance, insurance, and other related costs, which can significantly reduce net income.\n\nTo estimate maximum potential earnings per month, let's consider a driver working full-time hours, around 40 hours per week. If they earn $20 per hour on average (a midpoint estimate), their gross earnings would be $800 per week or roughly $3,200 per month. However, with expenses potentially reducing overall income by 20-30%, net earnings might be closer to $2,240 to $2,560 per month.\n\nDrivers who work more hours, drive during peak times, and/or optimize their strategies might earn more. Ride-sharing earnings can fluctuate, so it's essential for drivers to track their income and expenses carefully.",
